   enables energy management and simulation of new control policies in a
   city district. The proposed platform enables the interoperability and
   the correlation of (near-) real-time building energy profiles with
   environmental data from sensors as well as building and grid models. In
   a smart city context, this platform fulfills 1) the integration of
   heterogeneous data sources at the building and district level, and 2)
   the simulation of novel energy policies at the district level aimed at
   the optimization of the energy usage accounting also for its impact on
   building comfort. The platform has been deployed in a real-world
