Abstract = {{New technologies open up the door to multiple business models applied to
   public services in smart cities. However, there is not a commonly
   adopted methodology for evaluating business models in smart cities that
   can help both practitioners and researchers to choose the best option.
   This paper addresses this gap introducing the Business Model Evaluation
   Tool for Smart Cities. This methodology is a simple, organized, flexible
   and the transparent system that facilitates the work of the evaluators
   of potential business models. It is useful to compare two or more
   business models and take strategic decisions promptly. The method is
   part of a previous process of content analysis and it is based on the
   widely utilized Business Model Canvas. The evaluation method has been
   assessed by 11 experts and, subsequently it has been validated applying
