Abstract = {{Mixed traffic is a common phenomenon in developing countries such as
   China. Understanding bicycles' moving behavior when it conflicts with
   motor vehicles/bicycles/pedestrians at unsignalized intersections is
   important for developing mixed traffic flow simulation models.
   Observations and analysis of bicycle movements when they conflict with
   those of vehicles/pedestrians at mixed traffic unsignalized
   intersections were made in our study. Field data from actual bicycle
   movements were captured from video data. We then proposed a plausible
   cyclist conflict avoidance movement model in mixed traffic flow
   situations based on fuzzy logic and the discrete choice method. Field
