Number = {{6}},
Pages = {{851-858}},
Month = {{NOV-DEC}},
Abstract = {{This paper presents a method for analyzing social media and digital
   governance in smart cities. This research, after selecting a group of
   issues related to people's concerns about daily life in cities, makes
   use of Afinn lexicon as dictionary with sentiment score in order to
   recognize and measure the strength of individual words. The experiment
   retrieves different tweets classified by hashtags in a database and
   calculates an average sentiment. It involves some statistical processes
   for the recognition of the topics' sentiment: the calculation of the
   weighted average, the standard deviation, and the distribution among -5
   to +5, based on the score range used by the lexicon. Finally, human
   evaluation is used to compare results from the automatic system.}},
